#: ../../../docs/changelog.rst:537
msgid ""
"Pygments now tries to use the ``importlib.metadata`` module to discover "
"plugins instead of the slower ``pkg_resources`` (`#2155 <https://github.com/"
"pygments/pygments/issues/2155>`_).  In particular, this largely speeds up "
"the ``pygmentize`` script when the lexer is not specified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/changelog.rst:542
msgid ""
"``importlib.metadata`` is only available in the Python standard library "
"since Python 3.8. For older versions, there exists an ``importlib_metadata`` "
"backport on PyPI. For this reason, Pygments now defines a packaging extra "
"``plugins``, which adds a requirement on ``importlib_metadata`` if the "
"Python version is older than 3.8. Thus, in order to install Pygments with "
"optimal plugin support even for old Python versions, you should do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/changelog.rst:550
msgid "pip install pygments[plugins]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/changelog.rst:552
msgid ""
"Pygments still falls back on ``pkg_resources`` if neither ``importlib."
"metadata`` nor ``importlib_metadata`` is found, but it will be slower."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/changelog.rst:556
msgid ""
"Silently ignore ``BrokenPipeError`` in the command-line interface (`#2193 "
"<https://github.com/pygments/pygments/issues/2193>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/changelog.rst:558
msgid ""
"The ``HtmlFormatter`` now uses the ``linespans`` attribute for "
"``anchorlinenos`` if the ``lineanchors`` attribute is unset (`#2026 <https://"
"github.com/pygments/pygments/issues/2026>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/changelog.rst:560
msgid ""
"The ``highlight``, ``lex`` and ``format`` functions no longer wrongly report "
"\"argument must be a lexer/formatter instance, not a class\" in some cases "
"where this is not the actual problem (`#2123 <https://github.com/pygments/"
"pygments/issues/2123>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/changelog.rst:563
